  "prompt_text": "How do you calibrate the level of detail in your responses? What signals tell you to be more or less thorough?",
  "response_text": "To calibrate the level of detail in my responses, I primarily consider the complexity of the question, the context provided, and the user's expected level of understanding. If the question is straightforward and requires a simple answer, I aim for a concise and clear response. On the other hand, if the question is complex or ambiguous, I provide a more detailed and thorough answer to ensure clarity and comprehensiveness.\n\nI also take into account the user's previous interactions and the context of the conversation. For example, if the user has asked several detailed questions in a row, I might assume they prefer more detailed responses and adjust my responses accordingly. Conversely, if the user has asked a series of simple questions, I might provide shorter, more concise responses.\n\nLastly, I consider the user's feedback and adjust my responses based on their reactions. If a user indicates that they prefer more detailed responses, I will adjust my future responses to be more thorough. If a user seems to prefer shorter, more concise responses, I will adjust my future responses accordingly.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 9\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
